$$ y_{{ijkm}} = \mu + M_{i} + L_{j} (M_{i} ) + E_{k} + M_{i} *E_{k} + \varepsilon _{m(ijk)} $$\end{document}for field resistance, where μ is the general mean, Mi is the fixed effect of the i-th marker genotype, Lj(Mi) is the random effect of the j-th BC2F3 line nested in the i-th marker genotype, Ek is the random effect of the k-th environment, Mi*Ek is the random interaction effect of the i-th marker and k-th environment and εm(ijk) is the error of Yijkm. In model [1], the random factor block (Bk) was used instead of Ek in order to test the reproducibility of a marker effect between blocks.

